Sentencas: A novel dynamic micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (MT-SOFC) and stack model including an integrated cooling system is developed using a quasi three-dimensional, spatially resolved, transient thermodynamic, physical and electrochemical model that accounts for the complex geometrical relations between the cells and cooling-tubes.
Titulo: Dynamic model of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: The modeling approach includes a simplified tubular geometry and stack design including an integrated cooling structure, detailed pressure drop and gas property calculations, the electrical and physical constraints of the stack design that determine the current, as well as control strategies for the temperature.
Titulo: Dynamic model of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: Moreover, an advanced heat transfer balance with detailed radiative heat transfer between the cells and the integrated cooling-tubes, convective heat transfer between the gas flows and the surrounding structures and conductive heat transfer between the solid structures inside of the stack, is included.
Titulo: Dynamic model of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: The detailed model can be used as a design basis for the novel MT-SOFC stack assembly including an integrated cooling system, as well as for the development of a dynamic system control strategy.
Titulo: Dynamic model of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: The evaluated best-case design achieves very high electrical efficiency between around 75 and 55% in the entire power density range between 50 and 550 mW/cm(2) due to the novel stack design comprising an integrated cooling structure.
Titulo: Dynamic model of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack including an integrated cooling system
